<TEXT type="str">Tourists who go to the Taishan Mountain of Tai&apos;an, east China&apos;s Shandong Province, during the Spring Festival will be lucky to have the opportunity to watch shadow puppet performances, an intangible cultural heritage of China. 

Dozens of classic traditional Chinese stories are staged. 

The audience could also control the shadow puppets themselves to experience the fun. 

&quot;It&apos;s nice and funny. I like it very much!&quot; said a little boy. 

&quot;We can have contact with the traditional Chinese culture and feel our intangible cultural heritage in the playing. It is an edutainment activity,&quot; said a tourist. 

Shadow puppet, which is made from animal skin or paperboard into the shape of human beings. When the show is performing, the puppets are controlled by artists behind a white curtain, accompanied by local folk narration and melodies played by percussion and string instruments.</TEXT> 
